One Pan Noodle Bowl
  --Cook's Country
  
1/4 c hoisin sauce, divided
3 tbsp shoyu
2 tsp cornstarch
12 oz pork tenderloin, trimmed, halved lengthwise, and sliced crosswise 1/4" thick
2 1/4 c chicken broth
2 tbsp vegetable oil
4 oz white mushrooms, trimmed and sliced thin
1 tbsp grated fresh ginger
2 garlic cloves, minced
3x3oz packages ramen noodels, seasoning packets reserved for another use
12 oz broccoli florets, cut into 1" pieces
3 scallions, sliced thin on bias

Whisk 1 tbsp hoisin, 1 tbsp shyu, and cornstarch together in bowl. Add pork and toss to coat; set aside. Whisk broth, remaining 3 tbsp hoisin, and remaining shoyu together in second bowl; set aside. Heat 1 tbsp oil in 12" nonstick skillet over medium hugh heat until shimmering. Add mushrooms and cook until browned, ~5 min. Add ginger and garlic and cook until fragrant, ~30 s. Add broth mixture and bring to boil. Arrange noodles in skillet in single layer; cover and reduce heat to medium. Cook until noodles have softened on bottoms, tops will still be dry, ~3 min. Uncover skillet and flip noodles and stir to separate. Spread noodles in even layer and scatter broccoli over top. Cover and cook until noodles and broccoli are tender, ~3 min, tossing halfway through cooking. Divide noodle mixture evenly among individual bowls; tent with foil. Wipe skillet clean with paper towel. Heat remaining oil in now empty skillet over high heat until just smoking. Add pork in single layer, braking up any clumps, and cook without stirring until browned on bottom, ~1 min. Stir and continue to cook until pork is no longer pink, ~1 min. Divide pork among bowls. Sprinkle with scallions and serve.

